cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the deployment of base station-equipped UAVs in a cellular network and investigates the network performance in terms of coverage and energy consumption. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper deals with the deployment of unmanned aerial vehicles. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a software-based simulator for optimal UAV deployment scenarios. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses image processing functions to collect geospatial data and identify obstacles that can disrupt the line-of-sight communications between UAVs and ground users. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category as the paper uses the Google Earth Engine platform for geospatial data collection, but the focus is on network performance rather than graphics.
